        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 4:30PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 429 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bexar, or 12 miles west of Salem in Fulton County, moving east at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Heart...                          Byron...
Morriston...                      Glencoe...
Agnos...                          Flint Springs...
Wheeling...                       Union...
Salem in Fulton County...         Salem Airport...
Mitchell...                       Bexar...
Viola...                          Camp...
Horseshoe Bend...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
